description.value:
Digital photograph (colour); view of painted rock art on sandstone cave wall, showing myriad painted, infilled human figures, mythical creature, bird and negative handprints. Negative blown handprints in red are at left, right handprints, lower one superimposed by three smaller human figures. All human figures but for ‘swimming’ figures are upright, with the most prominent: At lower left, depicted as if running to right, at centre, in red with white adornments at knee and ankle, heads cut off by flaking, and at upper right, both red and grey-green with further adornments. Crowd of smaller human figures in a line stand along base of image. Bird figure, upright and facing left, is below lower handprint and mythical beast (mass of infilled torso intersecting with human figures) is at right centre. Several figures are horizontal with limbs contorted as if swimming. Wadi Sura, Egypt.
Scanned

description.value:
Digital photograph (colour); view of painted rock art on rock shelter wall showing at least 20 human figures and an unidentified shape, upright but for ‘swimming’ figures, infilled in red and grey-green. Largest figure is at top centre in red with adornments visible at shoulder, elbow, knee and ankle and on torso, as with second red figure with missing head at lower left, and more faded grey-green figure in centre. To right of top figure are large and small figures in both pigments (children?) and at centre are four figures depicted with limbs contorted as if swimming, facing right, with rightmost facing down. Unidentified shape is at centre right, resembling infilled red torso of quadruped (mythical creature?). Figures in lower half of image are eroded and faded. 5cm photo scale fitted at base of image. Cave of Swimmers, Wadi Sura, Egypt.

description.value:
Digital photograph (colour); view of painted rock art on a sandstone cave wall, showing one negative handprint and he painted, infilled figures of four humans and one bird. The handprint is quite faint and the outlines have been blown in brown pigment. To the left of the central hand print are two human figures painted in darker brown, upright and facing right, apparently running with arms and legs splayed. The right figure (woman?) has short appendages (breasts?) hanging from beneath the arms on either side and appears to be carrying something in the right hand. This object has a thin arc outline on one side and a bulbous, infilled object on the other (bow?). They are running toward three tiny human figures which superimpose the hand print and are pictured in a line, bent at the waist, upright and facing left toward the runners. To the lower right of these figures is the figure of a brown standing bird, upright and facing left. Cave of Swimmers, Wadi Sura, Egypt.
